      <p>
        <s>In this part of the scene 3, <ref target="a11lk2_1" type="character">Jory</ref> catches <ref target="a11lk2_1" type="character">Isaac</ref> and <ref target="a11lk2_1" type="character">Emily</ref> kissing.</s>
        <s>After <ref target="a11lk2_1" type="character">Amir</ref> comes in, <ref target="a11lk2_1" type="character">Jory</ref> tells him, but <ref target="a11lk2_1" type="character">Amir</ref> is in complete disbelief.</s>
      </p>
      <p>
        <s>Adding, <ref target="a11lk2_1" type="character">Emily</ref> and <ref target="a11lk2_1" type="character">Isaac</ref> deny their affair, which <ref target="a11lk2_1" type="character">Amir</ref> believes.</s>
        <s>He accuses <ref target="a11lk2_1" type="character">Jory</ref> of destroying his life, including his job and marriage.</s>
      </p>
      <p>
        <s>This event leads to <ref target="a11lk2_1" type="character">Isaac</ref> and <ref target="a11lk2_1" type="character">Jory</ref> leaving.</s>
        <s>Following, <ref target="a11lk2_1" type="character">Amir</ref> asks <ref target="a11lk2_1" type="character">Emily</ref> if she has an affair with <ref target="a11lk2_1" type="character">Isaac</ref>, what she admits.</s>
        <s>All of <ref target="a11lk2_1" type="character"><choice><orig>Amirs</orig><reg>Amir's</reg></choice></ref> build up anger is now exploding and he starts to beat up his wife, <ref target="a11lk2_1" type="character">Emily</ref>.</s>
        <s>Only after the last punch he realized what he just did.</s>
      </p>
